Dough based on:
http://laylita.com/recipes/2008/06/11/empanadas-mendocinas/

3 cups flour
1 egg yolk
1/2 cup (~100g) of grasa - lard or butter or mix of both
3/4 cup to 1 cup of warm milk
1/2 tsp salt

Makes about 15 empanada discs.


Fillings:

Carne: (3-4 empanadas):

1/2 pound ground chuck
1/2 onion
2 garlic cloves
some parseley
pepper, salt, red pepper / paprika, cumin
tomato paste
1 - 2 boiled eggs, sliced
1 - 2 olives per empanada


Choclo: (3-4 empanadas)

1/2 onion
some frozen corn

sautee, mix with shredded mozzarella, some cream


Jamon y queso: (3-4 empanadas)

ham in cubes / chunks
shredded mozzarella
fresh mozzarella


Ongos (4-5 empanadas)

1.5 lb baby portabello / crimini mushrooms, quartered
1/2 onion
2 minced garlic cloves
1/2 red pepper, roasted, skinned, sliced in 1inch strips
tomato paste
splash of red wine
1 boiled egg
2 olives per empanada


Cebolla

2 large yellow onions, sliced
sautee in butter, add oregano
swiss cheese


400 degrees F, 25 minutes
